http://www.snapsurveys.com/swh/surveylogin.asp?k=128524501923
Earlier this year, we wrote about our plans for Informs and the Virtual Training Suite.   Over the last few months we have been looking at options for developing a new membership business model to sustain the services after the funding [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>An online survey about the future of Informs and the Virtual Training Suite is available from:</p>
<p><a href="http://www.snapsurveys.com/swh/surveylogin.asp?k=128524501923">http://www.snapsurveys.com/swh/surveylogin.asp?k=128524501923</a></p>
<p>Earlier this year, we wrote about our plans for <a href="http://www.intute.ac.uk/blog/2010/03/04/informs-funding-news/">Informs </a>and the <a href="http://www.intute.ac.uk/blog/2010/03/05/virtual-training-suite-funding-news/">Virtual Training Suite</a>.   Over the last few months we have been looking at options for developing a new membership business model to sustain the services after the funding is withdrawn in July 2011, and we are now conducting market research to find out what our users think.</p>
<p>Our market research consultants, <a href="http://www.mindsetresearch.co.uk/">Mindset Research</a>, have developed an online survey, available via the link above.</p>
<p>We need as many responses as possible to inform the research,  so if you have used Informs or the Virtual Training Suite or if you are interested in the future direction for these services, we would welcome your input.</p>
<p>The survey covers both Informs and the Virtual Training Suite. You  can choose to answer questions about one or both of these products.</p>
<p>The survey will be open until midnight on Wednesday 6th October 2010.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.intute.ac.uk/blog/2010/09/28/survey-on-the-future-of-informs-and-the-virtual-training-suite/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
		<slash:comments>9</slash:comments>
